osophy career</b></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2" style="text-align:center"></td></tr><tr><th scope="row">Era</th><td class="category"><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Age_of_Enlightenment" title="Age of Enlightenment">Age of Enlightenment</a></td></tr><tr><th scope="row">Region</th><td class="category"><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Western_philosophy" title="Western philosophy">Western philosophy</a><br/><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./French_philosophy" title="French philosophy">French philosophy</a></td></tr><tr><th scope="row"><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./List_of_schools_of_philosophy" title="List of schools of philosophy">School</a></th><td class="category"><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Lumières" title="Lumières">Lumières</a><br/><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Philosophes" title="Philosophes">Philosophes</a><br/><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Deism" title="Deism">Deism</a><br/><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Classical_liberalism" title="Classical liberalism">Classical liberalism</a></td></tr><tr class="note"><th scope="row"><div style="padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;">Main interests</div></th><td><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Political_philosophy" title="Political philosophy">Political philosophy</a>, <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Literature" title="Literature">literature</a>, <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Historiography" title="Historiography">historiography</a>, <a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Biblical_criticism" title="Biblical criticism">biblical criticism</a></td></tr><tr><th scope="row"><div style="padding:0.1em 0;line-height:1.2em;">Notable ideas</div></th><td><a rel="mw:WikiLink" href="./Philosophy_of_history" title="Philosophy of history">Philosophy of history</a>,<sup about="#mwt244" class="mw-ref" id="cite_ref-1" rel="dc:references" typeof="mw:Extension/ref" data-mw='{"name":"ref","attrs":{},"body":{"id":"mw-reference-text-cite_note-1"}}'><a href="./Voltaire#cite_note-1" style="counter-reset: mw-Ref 1;"><span class="mw-reflink-text">[1]</span></a></sup> <a rel="mw:WikiLin